# ChunkViz

An open‑source Python toolkit to **visualize and evaluate chunking strategies** for long documents in retrieval‑augmented generation (RAG) pipelines.

## Install (editable)
```bash
pip install -e .
```

## Quickstart
```bash
# 1) Ingest (uses simple text extraction via pdfplumber)
chunkviz ingest data/samples --out data/parquet

# 2) Chunk with the fixed chunker (tokens)
chunkviz chunk --config data/configs/demo.yaml

# 3) Evaluate (dummy metric over gold spans if provided)
chunkviz eval --queries data/queries.jsonl --k 10 --report out/report.html

# 4) Visualize overlays
streamlit run apps/streamlit/App.py
```

> ⚠️ MVP notice: This is a runnable scaffold with a **FixedChunker** and basic PDF parsing/overlay.
Semantic/layout chunkers and adapters are stubbed for iteration.

## Why
Chunking is one of the largest hidden levers in RAG. ChunkViz makes it **visible and measurable**.

